description:
Batman finally knows who killed Vesper Fairchild, how they did it, and why they did it. And he needs the help of those close to him to bring the killer down - and to get this, he must first reconcile with them. Most of the legwork had been carried out by Batgirl, Nightwing, Alfred, Oracle and Robin, but for the first time everything is assembled:

Lex Luthor has been in constant conflict with Bruce Wayne since No Man's Land, and Wayne's opposition to his presidency made him decide to get rid of this irritation and pay for someone to perform a character assassination on the man. Through an agent known as Amherst, one of the world's top assassins was hired - David Cain, who also happens to be Batgirl's father and to have trained a young Bruce Wayne. Knowing of Wayne's other life, Cain decided to carry out the crime in a way which would expose his secret identity, or at worst create discord between him and those around him. For a time he succeeded, but now they must go after him - preferably without Batgirl.

However, when they find him, they instead find a series of doubles, and the real deal shows up at the Batcave and attacks Oracle - he had access to their communications channel. Thankfully, Batman had anticipated this, and is waiting in the shadows to take him on. Cain reveals his utter contempt for Batman/Wayne and tries to make him into what Cain is - but Batman refuses to go over the edge into unnecessary violence, and Cain soon hands himself over to the authorities. Luthor is not pleased, particularly because he cannot locate agent Amherst. Perhaps this is because he is in Arkham Asylum under a different name.
name: Courage

description: GROUPIES! Hey! Rock stars have groupies! Well, guess what? So do Superheroes. And when the biggest horndog in superherodom is found dead in his undies, guess who is called into investigate? That's right, Bat-Man. No, no, of course not Bat-Man, Bat-Man isn't anywhere in this book. That would be like the most massive copyright infringement in the history of history. But screw Bat-Man, because Walker and Deena are on the case!! And they are taken through the seedy and sexy underbelly of superhero fame on the trail of the groupie turned killer.
name: Little Deaths (Part 1)

description: This inticing special issue is told from the point of view of a super-hero groupie. A woman hellbent on having intimate experiences with super-powered people. Big clues abound in the latest murder case for Walker and Pilgrim as they investigate the murder of one of the world's most beloved superheroes, whose private life it seems had left something to be desired.
name: Little Deaths (Part 2)

description: This murder solved!...? The spectacular conclusion to POWERS most baudy storyline. As a super-hero who often hooked up with super-hero groupies, has been found dead. Walker and Pilgrim solve the case ... but wait till you see what they discover. As suprising a chapter in the Powers series as you are going to find. Nominated for two Harvey awards for comic excellence-best new series and best new talent.
name: Little Deaths (Part 3)

description:
Overview

POWERS IS BACK WITH A VENGEANCE!!

After a short hiatus, POWERS returns with a whole new case, a whole new murder, and a whole new direction.

One of the greatest supergroups of all time has broken up, and the split is NOT amicable. When the most public member of the group is violently murdered, the suspect list is a who's who of the most flamboyant and popular super-powered figures in the city.

It's cops and capes like you've NEVER seen before in the surprise hit from super-hot comic writer and Eisner Award winner Brian Michael Bendis (Ultimate Spider-Man titles, Daredevil, Alias) and full-color Art Deco comic artist Mike Avon Oeming (Bluntman and Chronic, Hammer of the Gods).
name: Supergroup (Part 1)

description: COME ON BOARD THE EISNER AWARD WINNER FOR BEST NEW SERIES!! SUPERGROUP CONTINUES! The dark side of the greatest supergroup of all time is in full view when the most public member of the group is violently murdered. The suspect list is a who's who of the most flamboyant and popular super-powered people in the city. It's cops and capes like you have NEVER seen them in the surprise hit of the from super hot comic writer and EISNER award winner Brian Michael Bendis (Ultimate Spiderman titles, Daredevil, Alias) and full color, art deco comic artist Mike Avon Oeming (Blunt man and Chronic, Hammer of the Gods).
name: Supergroup (Part 2)

description: THE EISNER AWARD WINNER FOR BEST NEW SERIES ERUPTS!! THE SUPERGROUP SAGA!! The dark side of the greatest supergroups of all time is in full view as the most public member of the group is violently murdered. The suspect list is a who's who of the most flamboyant and popular super-powered people in the city. Ever see a superhero car chase? Well, you will!! It's cops and capes like you have NEVER seen them in the surprise hit of the from super hot comic writer and EISNER award winner Brian Michael Bendis (Ultimate Spiderman titles, Daredevil, alias) and full color, art deco comic artist Mike Avon Oeming (Blunt man and Cronic, hammer of the gods) .
name: Supergroup (Part 3)

description: COME ON BOARD THE 2001 EISNER AWARD WINNER FOR BEST NEW SERIES!! THE SUPERGROUP SAGA!! One of the most powerful superheroes in the world is wanted for murder! Wanted, and on the lam. And hey, if a big time superhero like Boogiegirl doesn't want to be captured by the police- she won't be captured by the police. So now Walker and Deena have to roll up their sleeves and come up with a way to make her come to them. It's cops and capes like you have NEVER seen them in the surprise hit of the year from super hot comic writer and EISNER award winner Brian Michael Bendis (Ultimate Spiderman titles, Daredevil, alias) and full-color, art deco comic artist Mike Avon Oeming (Bluntman & Chronic, Hammer of the Gods) .
name: Supergroup (Part 4)

description: Heroes glide through the sky on lightning bolts and fire. Flamboyant villains attempt daring daylight robberies. God-like alien creatures clash in epic battle over the nighttime sky. And on the dirty city streets below, Detectives Christian Walker and Deena Pilgrim do their job, as special homicide officers in charge of cases that involve Powers. What is a cop's job like in a world where powers are par for the course? And what kind of cop is given the assignment? THE SUPER GROUP SAGA'S SHOCKING CONCLUSION! Fireworks!! That's right! Its been building and building and here it comes- as the Super Group homicide case twists around and around, the powers detectives finally turn on each other- and it doesn't end pretty, It's the issue you've been waiting for- it is finally here! Walker and Deena have it out!
name: Supergroup (Part 5)

description: Heroes glide through the sky on lightning bolts and fire. Flamboyant villains attempt daring daylight robberies. God-like alien creatures clash in epic battles over the nighttime sky. And on the dirty city streets below, Homicide Detective Christian Walker does his job. Walker is teamed up with spunky rookie Detective Deena Pilgrim to investigate murders specific to superhero cases. Investigations that take them from the seediest underbelly a city has to offer, to the gleaming towers that are home to immortal beings. It's cops-and-capes like you have NEVER seen them in the surprise hit from super- hot comic writer and EISNER award-winning team of Brian Michael Bendis (Ultimate Spider-Man, Daredevil, Alias) and full- color, art deco comic artist Mike Avon Oeming (Bluntman & Chronic, Hammer of the Gods). The Supergroup Saga Explosive Conclusion! One of the greatest supergroups in the world has been virtually destroyed in front of the world. But the fallout for Walker and Pilgrim is much more personal than they ever thought it would be. An issue that will change Powers forever!
name: Supergroup (Part 6)

description:
Overview

New regular penciller Scott Kolins joins as a new chapter in Wally West's life begins. The Flash comes to the horrifying conclusion that many people he's come into contact with and rescued over the years are being systematically murdered. Making matters worse, his ex-girlfriend Frances Kane -- Magenta -- has returned to plague him.
name: Blood Will Run I: Breaking the Foundation

description: Part 3 of the 4-part "Blood Will Run." Flash has been captured by the cult that's been murdering all the people of Keystone that the Scarlet Speedster has ever rescued. Now, alone, he faces Cicada, the creepy, charismatic leader of the cult, and the magnificently menacing Magenta!
name: Blood Will Run III: Close to Home

description: The conclusion to the 4-part "Blood Will Run." The Flash has found himself an uneasy idol of the murderous cult that has killed innocent victims in his name. This issue has everything, including Jesse Quick, Magenta, and a final-page cliffhanger that will send you reeling!
name: Blood Will Run (Part 4): Uneasy Idol

description:
Overview

In "Moving Right Along," the Flash (Wally West) and his lovely bride Linda take a break from all the recent action, watching their favorite hockey team play a game. But the fun is interrupted when the latest addition to the Rogues Gallery debuts.
name: Moving Right Along

description: A destructive storm has hit Keystone City, and the Flash must face the deadly Rogues Gallery member who's behind it. Streamlined for the new millennium, the Weather Wizard returns with a vengeance more masterful and mercenary than ever!
name: Birth Right Part 1: Eye of the Storm

description: Linda is protecting a baby who seems to have meta-human powers and the Weather Wizard wants complete control of the tot! Can the Flash keep the kid AND Keystone City safe from blizzards, howling winds, tornadoes, and hurricanes? "Birthright" part 2.
name: The Weather Wizard's Out For Blood

description: The Rogues begin their attack on the Flash's allies, starting with Chunk. A special bullet creates a problem with Chunk's powers and only the Flash can stop him from absorbing the whole city!
name: Event Horizion

description:
Every time he thinks he's out, they pull him back in - the Pied Piper, that is! As if Piper weren't in enough trouble already, the Joker's venomous plans strike Keystone City, transforming one of the Flash's greatest allies into a lethal, laughing Rogue! Plus, Iron Heights is under siege and a "Jokerized" Deadshot sets his sights on Captain Boomerang!

Deadline, Merlyn and Deadshot are coming to Keystone with smiles on their faces. The Flash must stop them from killing themselves and everyone around them as well.
name: Smile for the Camera

description: "Peekaboo" is the name of the latest Flash adversary, one we confidently predict will cause a sensation! Who is she? What's driven her to face the Flash in order to get what she wants? The answers are all in this issue!
name: Peek-A-Boo

description: DC FULL COVERAGE! Entry-point issue! The core of Iron Heights' power grid is energized by a former prisoner named Fallout. But Fallout has broken free of Keystone's horrifying penitentiary and wants to wreak havoc on the Flash's home city!
name: Fallout

description:
In "Absolute Zero," the Flash faces a difficult situation regarding one of his Rogues. Captain Cold may be a thief...but is he a murderer? Find out when Cold single-handedly tracks down the killer of someone very near and dear to him.

Notes:

  • Ranked #22 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".
name: Absolute Zero

concept_credits.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

first_appearance_concepts.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

description: The original Trickster retired long ago...but there's a newer, younger Trickster in Keystone City who's got a 21st-century bag of tricks - all of them with the aim of making Flash's life miserable!
name: Introducing the Trickster

description: The storyline that's been building slowly for months is unleashed with a vengeance, as the newly-formed Rogues' Gallery runs rampant through Central City. At the same time, the vicious criminal mastermind known as the Thinker claims Keystone!
name: Crossfire Part 1: Run Program

description: "Crossfire," Part 2 of 5. The Rogues control Central City. The Thinker controls all of Keystone! And the Flash has been infected with a "frenzy virus," courtesy of Murmur - the deadly and psychotic Rogue introduced in THE FLASH: IRON HEIGHTS!
name: Crossfire Part 2: Hide and Seek

description: "Crossfire," Part 3 of 5. The Thinker has "possessed" the Flash hoping to add Wally's speed to his computer-like mind. Meanwhile, the new Rogues run rampant throughout Central City!
name: Crossfire Part 3: The Thinking Man

description: In "The Bonds of Friends and Lovers," Kyle's life takes a dramatic turn when he receives some unexpected surprises from all the people around him, including his on-again off-again girlfriend Jade and Kyle's assistant, Terry. It's the not-to-be-missed issue of GREEN LANTERN that will have everyone talking!
name: The Bonds of Friends and Lovers

description: "Away From Home," Part 1 of 4. Kyle and Jade are sent to an exotic planet as ambassadors of peace. But when a terrorist act plunges an alien civilization into Civil War, will our heroes choose peace or will they choose to fight?
name: Away From Home (Part 1)

description: The conclusion of "Away From Home" (Pt. 2 of 2) finds Kyle and Jade fighting to stop terrorists who have uncovered an ancient mutagen that could make them unstoppable, as the once-peaceful resort world plunges into bloody civil war.
name: Away From Home, part 2

description: Green Lanterns Kyle Rayner and Jade take on a mysterious and quick-moving arsonist who's trying to set New York ablaze. But the beings responsible for torching Manhattan are more than capable of taking on two Green Lanterns!
name: House on Fire, part 1

description: The trio known as Inferno is more than a match for two Green Lanterns, so Jade is in serious trouble when Kyle gets critically injured and taken out of the fight! Jade's got no time to help him out though, as Inferno's three members ? Ember, Torch and Blaze ? try to take out not only two Green Lanterns in one day, but all of Manhattan!
name: House on Fire, part 2

description: Kyle's powers have been increasing with experience, but his most recent adventures have pushed him farther than he's ever gone before, and he may not be coming back! Jade, Sentinel and former Green Lantern John Stewart have to figure out how to make sure Kyle's mind stays intact while Kyle struggles for control over a power that is too much for one person.
name: The Battle of Fire and Light, part 1

description: A DC Full Coverage! entry-point issue. It's the end of an era for Kyle Rayner, and the beginning of something far more dangerous than he's ever had to deal with. The Guardians of the Universe created the Green Lanterns to maintain order and peace, while their polar opposites, the Qwardians, believed only in bringing about disorder and chaos. Now their champions - Kyle and Nero - battle for control of the greatest source of power either of them has ever had access to. To the victor go the spoils, but the prize may prove too grand for either man to handle.
name: Battle of Fire and Light, part 2

description: Kyle Rayner is going through an incredible metamorphosis as all the power that he, his ring, and therefore all the incarnations of Green Lanterns before him converge under his control. Is the real question here can he control this much power, or should he?
name: Hand of God, Day One

description: Wheelchair-bound former Green Lantern John Stewart confronts his deepest, darkest secrets ? a twisted journey through the psyche of a man who has had it all and lost it all. Meanwhile, the current Green Lantern, Kyle Rayner, spreads his newfound wings into near-godhood.
name: Standing Up

description: Guest-starring Superman and featuring the return of Jade! Before Jenny Lynn-Hayden took up the Green Lantern ring, she was simply Jade. Given powers through her lineage, she lost them protecting her father. All this may be changing thanks to the scope of Kyle (now known as Ion) and his new powers. But as Ion's abilities increase, the concerns over whether or not Kyle should be trusted with this ultimate power grows in all of his peers.
name: Hand of God, Day Three: Lost and Found

description: Guest-starring the JLA! Kyle's newfound powers as Ion may be the only thing that can help the JLA stop an alien invasion! But if that's true, why doesn't the JLA approve of what Kyle is doing? Kyle is forced to look at the way his god-like actions are affecting the world around him. If Superman can't convince Kyle to think twice about his world-changing deeds, then who can?
name: Hand of God, Day Four

description: Extra-sized issue! The end of Ion! The return of Green Lantern! But just who is going to wear the Green Lantern ring? As Kyle visits the moments in the past when various heroes have been given the Green Lantern ring, he must decide exactly how he can best serve the cause of good. With appearances from Hal Jordan (now the Spectre), Alan Scott, John Stewart, Guy Gardner, and others, this issue is the beginning of a whole new Green Lantern!
name: Beginning's End

description:
The future of all Green Lanterns begins here! In the aftermath of the "Hand of God" story line, we find a Green Lantern with a new outlook on his duties, as well as new tricks up his sleeve. There's not going to be any rest for anyone, however, as an infectious madness without rhyme or reason grabs hold of New York City, starting with one of Earth's former Green Lanterns!

Downtown Manhattan, 10:37 am- Kyle Rayner, as the Green Lantern, stops a bunch of armature bank robbers and stops a half naked man from stealing a woman's purse, who turns out to be a well off business man who lost his sanity.

Kyle then goes to Feast Magazine for a meeting with Rena Stone. While there he meets up with Terry Berg and they go to the meeting together. While in the meeting Rena starts acting weird, and starts undressing in front to the two artists. She soon realizes what she is doing and stops, but before Kyle can help her get redressed, there is a commotion in the other room.

Mike Dennis, has striped almost naked and is smashing his computer. Kyle tries to stop him but is alerted to the events outside. Everyone outside is going crazy, so Kyle changes into the Green Lantern and flies into action. Soon he releases green constructs, much like his are causing a lot of damage. So like a good superhero he follows them to the source and soon learns that a insane Jade behind the green constructs, and he his helpless to help her.
name: Back in the Saddle

description:
Green Lantern, Sentinel and Jade have their hands full trying to save New York from itself! An uncontrollable madness has gripped the citizens of New York, and not even the combined might of our heroes will be able to control it. Things go from bad to way, way, way worse as the source of the insanity comes forward, with a power that no Green Lantern can stop!

S.T.A.R. Labs- Jade is under the watchful eye Dr. Emmil Brown, Kyle Rayner and her father Alan Scott. Dr Brown is still unsure what is causing her hallucinations, but is finding that over a thousand other people are suffering from the same symptoms as Jade but without her powers. Kyle and Alan are soon on the streets of the city protecting the citizens.

The pair don't see eye to eye on how to deal with the situation, and Alan is suddenly affected by hallucinations and turns on Kyle. The two Green Lanterns start to battle. Meanwhile back at the lab Jade wakes up and says "Henry is back". That is when Brainwave Jr. steps out of Alan's head.

Brainwave Jr. tells his origin and how he got his powers and turned on his friends. He then uses Alan's body to attack Kyle, and is about kill Kyle when Jade steps in and attempts to knock out Brainwave Jr. from behind. She is able to hit him but Brainwave Jr. is able to quickly regain the upperhand and over whelms Kyle, Alan and Jade's minds. While the three lay prone, Brainwaves Jr. leaves saying he has more important chores to do.
name: Out of Our Heads

description: The incredible planet Mercury host the the challenge of the Flash . But Wally isn't prepared when future versions of both Heatwave and Captain Cold break the rules.
name: One Million

description:
A nuclear launch on the United States has been ordered... World War III is imminent... And the only ones who have a prayer of stopping Armageddon are the X-Men! And while Cyclops, Marvel Girl, Storm, Beast, Iceman, and Colossus battle S.H.I.E.L.D., Wolverine battles the one foe he's never beaten: Sabretooth!

Wolverine and Sabretooth battle and Wolverine wins.

The Brotherhood free the X-Men and togeather take down Weapon X.
name: End Game

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: THE SCOOP: Hide your valuables and lock up your daughters, it's the ultimate version of Gambit! ? THE STORY: He's charming. He's dangerous. He survives on wits alone. He's Gambit -- and he could be the next X-Man! That is, if the team can convince him to join! And if he doesn't get himself killed helping a fellow street urchin! And if Storm and Professor X can actually find him! Whew, sounds like guest-writer Chuck Austen (U.S. WAR MACHINE) and guest-artist Essad Ribic (BROTHERHOOD) have really stacked the deck against Gambit!?
name: Thief in the Night

story_arc_credits.name: You Always Remember Your First Love

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: You Always Remember Your First Love

description: THE SCOOP: Part two of the introduction of Ultimate Gambit! ? THE STORY: Against all better judgment, street urchin Remy LeBeau has taken in a young girl in trouble. Now, he's pursued by the killers desperate to find her. He's always relied only on himself, keeping at arm's length from entangling relationships. Now, will opening his heart result in his death?
name: Wild Card

story_arc_credits.name: You Always Remember Your First Love

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: You Always Remember Your First Love

description: THE SCOOP: A new direction starts here! ? THE STORY: For the first time, see exactly what Charles Xavier has been teaching the X-Men! Read the Xavier Institute's mission statement, as we head directly into a new story arc that will take the mutants on an international "fieldtrip" from Russia to Scotland to Australia! Plus: What is Xavier's greatest secret?
name: It Doesn't Have to be This Way

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: THE SCOOP: A new story begins here! ? THE STORY: It's the first step on Charles Xavier's big global field trip, as the X-Men jet off to Scotland... and meet one of Professor X's old flames! What is the top secret project she's working on... and how is it linked to the biggest secret of the mutant world?
name: World Tour: Part 1

description: THE SCOOP: Part II of the Proteus Saga! ? THE STORY: How do you fight a foe that can warp reality, place his essence in another body, and shield himself from Xavier's mental attacks? Find out when the X-Men face the most danerous mutant alive ? Proteus! Plus: where is Colossus? And what's up with Jean Grey's strange psychic flashes?
name: World Tour: Part 2

description: THE SCOOP: The X-Men World Tour rages on! ? THE STORY: The students hit Colossus's home turf -- and wait until you see how the steel-skinned strongman handles the visit! Plus: Professor X's biggest secret comes back to haunt him -- with a vengeance!?
name: World Tour: Part 3

description:
The frenzied field trip comes to a spectacular climax as four of our beleagured mutants fight for their lives against the greatest threat yet! Plus: A new member debuts!

En route to the airport, some of the X-men wonder, whether Xavier isn't mentally influencing them to play heroes. They are interrupted as David attacks them in Betsy Braddock's body.

After shrugging off an attack by Wolverine, David singles out Beast promising him a world that will accept him, if he joins David's side. When this doesn't work, David tells him that his relationship with Storm is a fake.

Brushing off an attack by Storm, David destroys the plane, the other X-men are on, but teleports them out first, as he wants their deaths to be personal. He intends to take over Cyclops, when suddenly he feels weakened.

When he gets close to killing Storm, Iceman gets over his hysteria, which kept him out of the fight to attack David but to no avail, as David hurts the young boy badly. David then teleports himself and Xavier to each of the planned stops of the book tour, murdering dozens of people everywhere, before teleporting them back to Berlin, where he intends to kill his father.

However the personality of Betsy Braddock comes to the fore, weakening him. Betsy begs Xavier to kill them. Xavier is unable to act; Colossus however is not as he smashes Betsy/David with a car.

Some days later at David's funeral, Xavier decides, he's been dangerously nave and that he will disband the X-men.
name: World Tour: Part 4

description: THE SCOOP: It's the electric epilogue to the X-Men's World Tour! ? THE STORY: Due to the events of the World Tour, Professor X is all alone -- and at an all-time low -- in New York City. And while the X-Men fight for their lives elsewhere, the Brotherhood finally gets their act together... and that's a bad thing for the good guys!
name: Resignation

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
The third thrilling collection of the critically acclaimed, award-winning PROMETHEA is back, offered as a softcover version of the original hardcover!

PROMETHEA BOOK THREE is a 224-page trade paperback from AMERICA'S BEST COMICS reprinting PROMETHEA #13-18, written by Alan Moore with art and cover by J.H. Williams III & Mick Gray.

Featuring the first half of a cosmic road trip, this volume finds Promethea and Barbara traveling an unlikely path. Their wanderings take them through the many realms of Heaven and Hell, visiting manifestations of great visions and visionaries. Meanwhile, back on Earth, Stacia is the acting Promethea protecting and serving the people of New York while Promethea is away. Is she up to the task?
name: Book Three

description: Megatron's sinister plan continues to unfold, putting the entire world at risk! Can Prime and the Autobots stop him, especially when the pandemonium gets worse because of the Devastator? What happens when Prime's most loyal soldiers refuse to fight?
name: Prime Directive; Part 4

description: With Optimus Prime left for dead and the world on the brink of collapse, the battered and beaten Autobot warriors must battle on against the evil Decepticons! Can they stop Megatron's evil cyber-virus before it is too late? Plus, details about Spike's secret informant revealed! The action reaches a fever pitch in issue #5 of the most popular comic book event of the year! Don't miss out on Transformers: Generation 1!
name: Prime Directive; Part 5

description: Join Dreamwave for the dramatic conclusion to the comic book event of the year! Can Optimus Prime and the Autobots stop Megatron's evil plan in time? And what will they have to sacrifice to do it? You won't want to miss the action-packed final showdown! The world of Transformers will never be the same! This issue features two different covers by Pat Lee. Each also contains a different mini-poster for each cover!
name: Prime Directive; Part 6
Mother Goose and Nursery Rhyme Comics

The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

first_appearance_characters.name: The Cow who Jumped over the Moon
The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

name: Felix the Cat and the Haunted Castle

description: The 22 Brides are a rock band/ group of assassins.
name: Married To The Mob: Shades of Red
Married To The Mob Part 2: Lipstick Bullets
Married To The Mob Part 3: Thighmaster Proxy
Married To The Mob Part 4: Marinara Macarena!

description: PREACHER's Garth Ennis tells a wild tale of WWII that reads something like The Dirty Dozen remade by Monty Python!
name: Once More Unto the Breach

description: The ultra-top-secret British Commando Unit known as the Rifle Brigade has fallen into the hands of Gerta Gash, a cunning dominatrix with unspeakable ways of making them talk. Can our heroes keep a stiff upper lip for Mother England? Or will Gerta's rigorous efforts eventually break their weakest link?
name: Definitely Not Cricket

description: "Up Yours Fritz," the riotous conclusion to the over-the-top miniseries! On the eve of D-Day, Capt. Darcy and his crew rumble with "Jager X," a squad of monstrous Nazi paratroopers ? in the fuselage of a Nazi bomber! Can our heroes stem the Nazi tide at thirty-thousand feet?
name: Up Yours, Fritz

description: "E.T. Go Home" With this issue, Barry Ween makes the jump from Image to Oni Press. Running from mob bosses that he had scammed, a mysterious, yet oddly familiar creature crash-lands on Earth, attracting the attention of the foul-mouthed Barry Ween, who must battle heavily armed aliens.
name: E.T. Go Home

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius 2.0

description: Humor abounds in this untitled story, which finds Barry Ween and his friend Jeremy inadvertently transported back in time to the Old West.

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius 2.0

description: Target: Ween" The government mistakes Jeremy for Barry when trying to capture Barry in order to use his brain.
name: "Target: Ween" Or "The Truth Is Out There With Men In Black Who Trust No One"

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius 2.0

description: "Gorilla in our Midst" During a class field trip to the zoo, Barry meets a gorilla from the alternate dimension of Bezeruul. Barry also battles aliens.
name: Gorilla in Our Midst

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius 3: Monkey Tales

description: "Your Feets Too Big" Barry's family and Jeremy go camping, where they meet a female Bigfoot named Roxie, who can read. Roxie becomes a regular cast member.
name: Your Feets Too Big

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius 3: Monkey Tales

description: "Outbreakdance" A virus-carrying monkey escapes the school lab, but Barry saves the day by developing a serum. Less easy to deal with is sex education and the forthcoming school dance.
name: Outbreakdance

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius 3: Monkey Tales

description: "Adventures in BarrySitting." This flashback issue finds a five-year-old Barry meeting his neighbor Jeremy, who has overprotective parents. Sarah gets sucked into a wormhole.
name: Adventures in BarrySitting

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius 3: Monkey Tales

description: "Our Little Girl's All Grown Up, or, That Tale of the Great Ape, Part Two" After following Sarah through an interdimensional wormhole, Barry and Jeremy meet up with a decidedly adult Sarah, who doesn't want to go home.
name: Our Little Girl's All Grown Up

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius 3: Monkey Tales

description: "The Tale of the Great Ape, Part Three: The Fastest Runner Who's Not Allowed to Win"
name: The Fastest Runner Who is Not Allowed to Win, The Tale Of The Great Ape -- Part Three

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius 3: Monkey Tales

description: "Time Lord." Featuring the first appearance of Barry Ween, a funny, foul-mouthed 10-year-old with a 350 I.Q., this issue finds the titular character inadvertently opening an interdimensional wormhole in his parent's basement. Naturally, Barry and pal Jeremy go in to investigate.
name: Time Lord

volume.name: The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius
